<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
45. 
<taxonomicName LSID="D67EC4FB-138C-5608-A82A-670B69806CB2" authority="B. B. Liu &amp; J. Wen, nom. nov. [Note R]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rhaphiolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhaphiolepis yui" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yui">Rhaphiolepis yui B.B.Liu &amp; J.Wen, nom. nov. [Note R]</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1821" authorityName="J.Lindley" authorityYear="1821" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Eriobotrya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriobotrya kwangsiensis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kwangsiensis">Eriobotrya kwangsiensis</taxonomicName>
Chun ex X.H.Yang &amp; S.Q.Lin, Acta Hortic. 750: 221. 2007. Type: China. Guangxi: Xiangzhou County, Shangguchen, Wuzhishan, 18 June 1936, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C. Wang 39423</emphasis>
(holotype: IBK [barcode IBK00061038, herbarium accession number 35925]!; isotypes: PE [barcode 00799311]!, SZ [barcode 00194327]). [Note S]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">China (Guangxi).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="note r">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Note R.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The species epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1821" authorityName="J.Lindley" authorityYear="1821" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Eriobotrya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="kwangsiensis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kwangsiensis">kwangsiensis</taxonomicName>
&quot; has been pre-occupied by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu" authorityYear="1932" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rhaphiolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhaphiolepis kwangsiensis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kwangsiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Rhaphiolepis kwangsiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hu, J. Arnold Arbor. 13: 335. 1932, thus a new name is needed for this taxon (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B42" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, D, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, 2018. International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The epithet is given in honor of the late Prof. Te-Tsun Yu (PE) for his great contributions to the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindl. in Bot. Reg.: ad t. 468. 1 Jul" authorityYear="1820" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rhaphiolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="note s">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Note S.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.17660/ActaHortic.2007.750.34" author="Yang, XH" editor="Huang, XM" journalOrPublisher="ISHS Acta Horticulturae, Guangzhou" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="221 - 224" refId="B54" refString="Yang, XH, Lin, SQ, 2007. The identity of Eriobotrya kwangsiensis chun, sp. n. In: Huang, XM, Janick, J, Eds., II International Symposium on Loquat 750. ISHS Acta Horticulturae, Guangzhou: 221 - 224, DOI: https://doi.org/10.17660/ActaHortic.2007.750.34" title="The identity of Eriobotrya kwangsiensis chun, sp. n." url="https://doi.org/10.17660/ActaHortic.2007.750.34" volumeTitle="II International Symposium on Loquat 750." year="2007">Yang and Lin (2007)</bibRefCitation>
provided the following type information in the protologue, &quot;Guangxi: Shangguchen. 1936. 6. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C. Wang 35925</emphasis>
(Holotypus, TBK)&quot;. According to the image of holotype provided in the protologue, the holotype is 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C. Wang 39423</emphasis>
, which was deposited in the herbarium IBK rather than TBK (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype of Rhaphiolepis yui (IBK [barcode IBK 00061038])." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.154.52790.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/438841" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">2</figureCitation>
). The number 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“35925”">&quot;35925&quot;</normalizedToken>
cited in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.17660/ActaHortic.2007.750.34" author="Yang, XH" editor="Huang, XM" journalOrPublisher="ISHS Acta Horticulturae, Guangzhou" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="221 - 224" refId="B54" refString="Yang, XH, Lin, SQ, 2007. The identity of Eriobotrya kwangsiensis chun, sp. n. In: Huang, XM, Janick, J, Eds., II International Symposium on Loquat 750. ISHS Acta Horticulturae, Guangzhou: 221 - 224, DOI: https://doi.org/10.17660/ActaHortic.2007.750.34" title="The identity of Eriobotrya kwangsiensis chun, sp. n." url="https://doi.org/10.17660/ActaHortic.2007.750.34" volumeTitle="II International Symposium on Loquat 750." year="2007">Yang and Lin (2007)</bibRefCitation>
was the herbarium accession number of the holotype.
</paragraph>
